properties.Name: DunBradstreetJudgment
properties.Description:
Judgments are final decision of a court resolving a dispute and determining the rights and obligations of the parties. 

A judgment may or may not have been initiated through a lawsuit. Judgment satisfaction occurs when the rights of the prevailing parties have been restored and any obligations have been paid. 

A satisfaction of judgment is then filed with the court of record. Vacated judgments are considered cancelled or rescinded. 

Stayed judgments are suspended and prevailing parties are refrained from enforcing it for the time period designated by the court.

Columns.Name: DunsNumber
Columns.Description: Dun & Bradstreet (D&B) provides a D-U-N-S Number, a unique nine digit identification number, for each physical location of your business.

Columns.Name: ReportPurchaseDate
Columns.Description: The purchase date of the report.

Columns.Name: DateFiled
Columns.Description: The date the judgment was filed.

Columns.Name: JudgmentAgainName
Columns.Description: The name of the party that the judgment was filed against.

Columns.Name: FiledWithName
Columns.Description: The name of the court with whom the judgment was filed.

Columns.Name: FiledAtCity
Columns.Description: The city at which the judgment was filed.

Columns.Name: FiledAtState
Columns.Description: The state at which the judgment was filed.

Columns.Name: InFavorOfPlaintiffIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates whether the judgment was awarded in favor of the plaintiff or not.

Columns.Name: StatusAttainedDate
Columns.Description: The date of the judgment's status.

Columns.Name: DunBradstreetJudgmentStatusTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Dun Bradstreet Judgment Status Type.
